<br>
Myself, I love it and so do most the Necromancers I know but then I am in a primary raiding guild.  I would much rather be a steady high sustained damage dealer then a third rate utility class.  There just is not call for such a class, espically in PoP.  You are not really going to do much without a serious healer or Mez'ing class.<br>
<br>
The change is kind of like what Mages have gone thru.  SoE steped up the temp of the game with PoP, along with some classes that were starting to fall behind.  We lose some utility and some solo options but in return we gained alot of damage output in groups.  <br>
<br>
Lets face it, unless SoE was willing to upgrade Necromancer healing to near Druid/Shaman level and seriously improve our mez ability (heck, we only had ONE mez spell to begin with...) then that utility was going to become extinct anyways.  It was already starting to towards the later end of Luclin.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>- Let the stat taps hit pets too.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Actually I wish all group and AE buffs worked upon pets.  They are after all affected by all adverse AE attacks, so it is only fair that pets should get the benefit of AE buffs aswell.  SoE once mentioned that they were looking into this but it appears to have fallen to the side.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Let's not fall prey to the illusion that VI is listening and cares.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I think that is a pretty closeminded opinion.  SoE has made some very drastic changes to the game based purily upon player input.  Considering they continue to claim that EQ I will remain as long as there is a player base for it and the rumors of yet another expansion, I am pretty sure that SoE is listening they just may not answer or not give an answer you wish to hear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Necromancers, nor any pet class, have ever had a problem with sustaining damage output.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Your forgetting that Necromancers until very recently had very weak DD ability (below that of Chanters and Clerics) and your average group made DoTs mana ineffectient because they would hardly reach their full duration.    <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Of course, this ability is negated in most fights that don't last longer than 2 minutes.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Correct. Unless the fight was long enough to allow for DoT stacking, DD has always been a better means of damage.  A lack of DD has always been a weakness in the Necromancer class until recently.  Not to mention the imbalanced power between DD and DoTs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Due to the Flexability of Necromancers other abilities, I don't believe they should be on that top rung all the time.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I am not saying they belong in your top rung either, what I am saying is you can not group classes like that because they excel at different types of damage.  A Wizard excels at burst damage but are pretty weak are sustained damage.  <br>
<br>
Your attempting to draw parallels that can not be made.  Wizards should be the undisputed masters of quick damage but not the masters of all types of damage.  Your trying to mix types into one category.<br>
<br>
Bril<br>
<br>
